com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.os
Interface OperatingSystem

All Superinterfaces:
com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability, com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.DeployModelObject, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Subinterfaces:
AIXOperatingSystem, LinuxOperatingSystem, RedhatLinuxOperatingSystem, SUSELinuxOperatingSystem, WindowsOperatingSystem
All Known Implementing Classes:
AIXOperatingSystemImpl, LinuxOperatingSystemImpl, OperatingSystemImpl, RedhatLinuxOperatingSystemImpl, SUSELinuxOperatingSystemImpl, WindowsOperatingSystemImpl
public interface OperatingSystem
extends com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability

A representation of the model object 'Operating System'.

The following features are supported:

  • Fqdn
  • Hostname
  • Kernel Architecture
  • Kernel Version
  • Kernel Width
  • Locale
  • Manufacturer
  • Os Distribution
  • Os Servicepack
  • Os Type
  • Os Version
  • Time Zone

See Also:
OsPackage.getOperatingSystem()

Returns the value of the 'Fqdn' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Fqdn' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

Fully qualified domain name. e.g. "foo.watson.ibm.com." In practice the trailing "." is often omitted.

java.lang.String getHostname()
Returns the value of the 'Hostname' attribute.

If the meaning of the 'Hostname' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

A hostname, which could be a simple hostname or qualified name up to a full fqdn. In many operating systems, what would be returned by "hostname" from a command line.
